# 02 - RDP Brute Force & Active Directory Attack Detection

## Overview
This documents a simulated RDP brute force attack against a domain-joined Windows 10 machine using Crowbar and xfreerdp from a Kali Linux attacker machine. Active Directory was configured with a Windows Server 2022 domain controller. All activity was detected and logged using Sysmon and Splunk. Atomic Red Team was used to simulate additional adversary techniques.

## Lab Environment

| Role | OS | IP |
|------|----|----|
| Attacker | Kali Linux | 192.168.10.250 |
| Target | Windows 10 | 192.168.10.5 |
| Domain Controller | Windows Server 2022 | 192.168.10.7 |
| SIEM | Ubuntu 22.04 (Splunk) | 192.168.10.10 |

**Tools Used:** Crowbar, xfreerdp, Splunk Enterprise, Splunk Universal Forwarder, Sysmon (Olaf Hartong config), Atomic Red Team

## Attack Steps

### 1. Active Directory Setup
Configured Windows Server 2022 as a domain controller for mydfir.local. Created organizational units (IT, HR) and domain users.

### 2. Configure Logging
Installed Splunk Universal Forwarder and Sysmon on both Windows 10 and Windows Server. Configured inputs.conf to forward Security, Application, System, and Sysmon logs to the Splunk server at index=endpoint.

### 3. RDP Brute Force
Configured a static IP on Kali Linux and installed Crowbar. Enabled RDP on the Windows 10 target and added the domain user to the Remote Desktop Users group. Simulated a brute force attack against the target using a password list.

### 4. Atomic Red Team
Installed Invoke-AtomicRedTeam on Windows 10 and ran the following tests:
- **T1136.001** - Create Local Account: simulated attacker creating a backdoor admin account (NewLocalUser)
- **T1059.001** - PowerShell execution: simulated malicious PowerShell commands

## Detection

### RDP Brute Force Detection
Searched Splunk for failed and successful RDP login events:
- `index=endpoint EventCode=4625` - Failed login attempts from 192.168.10.250
- `index=endpoint EventCode=4624 jsmart` - Successful RDP login from Kali

### Atomic Red Team Detection
- `index=endpoint EventCode=4720` - New user account creation (NewLocalUser) detected
- `index=endpoint source="XmlWinEventLog:Microsoft-Windows-Sysmon/Operational"` - Sysmon captured process creation events during PowerShell execution tests
